{
  "texts": [
    "HFL combines data from entities, institutions, or data owners with the same features but different samples.",
    "An example of HLF is the collaboration of two medical institutions.",
    "Since their data are very similar, the feature space could be the same (Nasr et al. 2019).",
    "VFL assumes semi-honest behavior of the participants; that is, adversaries can only learn from corrupted parties, but not the data from other parties.",
    "VFL combines data from entities with the same sample IDs but distinct features."
  ]
}